org.fosstrak.reader.rprm.core
Class DataSelector

java.lang.Object
  org.fosstrak.reader.rprm.core.DataSelector

public class DataSelector
extends java.lang.Object

DataSelector objects are used to define what data shall be reported in notification messages or by commands that take a DataSelector object as parameter. Only events and data fields that are added to the respective lists shall be reported.

Author:
Markus Vitalini

Method Detail

create

public static DataSelector create(java.lang.String name,
                                  ReaderDevice readerDevice)
                           throws ReaderProtocolException
The static method to create an instance of a dateselector. If this method terminates successfully, the data selector is added to the list of dataselectors in the reader device. If a dataselector with the same name exists, an exception ("ERROR_OBJECT_EXISTS") is thrown.

Parameters:
name - The name of the dataselector
readerDevice - The reader device the dataselector belongs to
Returns:
The instance of the dataselector
Throws:
ReaderProtocolException - "ERROR_OBJECT_EXISTS"
